<% content_for :header do %>
  <h1>Factlink on your site</h1>
<% end %>

<% content_for :title do %>
  Factlink &mdash; On your site
<% end %>

<% content_for :content do %>
  <div class="on-your-site-intro">
    <h1 class="on-your-site-title">Empower your visitors</h1>
    <p>Give people more control over the content that is on your website. Let your visitors discuss about specific statements within your page. Factlink is a powerfool tool to determine the reliability of the sources you aggregate. Using Factlink will not only generate more traffic to your website but also increases your authority on the subjects your writing about.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="grid-2-col">
      <h1 class="on-your-site-title">Factlink plugin</h1>
      <div class="on-your-site-box">
        <p>Here are instructions
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid-2-col others-column">
      <h1 class="on-your-site-title">Wordpress plugin</h1>
      <p>This plugin enables you to create and view Factlinks on your WordPress website. You can annotate any statement on your website by selecting the statement and clicking the add Factlink button.
      </p>
      <a class="button blue" href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/factlink/">Use wordpress plugin</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="on-your-site-buttons">
    <h1 class="on-your-site-title">Factlink counter</h1>
    <p>Add the factlink counter to your website. The Factlink counter enables users to identify the Factlinks on your webpage.
    </p>
  </div>
<% end %>
